title: Terrell, Bogan lead Western Michigan over Ohio, 49-14
text:
Facebook Email Twitter Google+ LinkedIn Pinterest Terrell, Bogan lead Western Michigan over Ohio, 49-14 Zach Terrell accounted for four touchdowns, and Jamauri Bogan ran for a career-high 135 yards and a score Post to Facebook Terrell, Bogan lead Western Michigan over Ohio, 49-14 Zach Terrell accounted for four touchdowns, and Jamauri Bogan ran for a career-high 135 yards and a score   Freep.com: http://on.freep.com/1LAAav4     Terrell, Bogan lead Western Michigan over Ohio, 49-14 Associated Press 4:19 p.m. EDT October 17, 2015 Western Michigan running back Jamauri Bogan plays against Ohio State during an NCAA college football game Saturday, Sept. 26, 2015, in Columbus, Ohio. (Photo: Jay LaPrete, Associated Press) 
Zach Terrell accounted for four touchdowns, and Jamauri Bogan ran for a career-high 135 yards and a score to help Western Michigan beat Ohio 49-14 on Saturday. 
Terrell completed 14 of 20 passes for 137 yards and three touchdowns and added 4-yard scoring run. 
LeVante Bellamy had 149 yards rushing and a touchdown, and Jarvion Franklin added 95 yards and a score for Western Michigan (3-3, 2-0 Mid-American Conference). The Broncos, who came into the game averaging 123.8 yards rushing per game, ran for a season-high 430 yards — 401 in the second half. 
Terrell threw first-half touchdown passes of 7 and 27 yards to Daniel Braverman as Western Michigan took a 14-7 lead into the break. Bogan’s 67-yard scoring run on the opening possession of the second half was the Broncos longest play from scrimmage this season and capped the first of five-consecutive Western Michigan touchdown drives. 
Jordan Reid had 109 yards receiving for Ohio (5-2, 3-1).
